"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-komorebi-is-the-official-clothing-partner-of-nepali-team-for-paris-olympics\", \"text\": \"Subscribe Now  NOC signs four-year partnership deal with French apparel brand Komorebi  KATHMANDU, March 4: Nepal Olympic Committee (NOC) has signed an agreement with French apparel brand Komorebi as the official clothing partner of Nepal for the 33rd Summer Olympics in Paris, France. NOC Secretary General Nilendraraj Shrestha and Daniel Valetin, CEO for Komorebi, signed the agreement on behalf of their respective organizations on Sunday.  As per the agreement, Komorebi will provide sports dress to the members of the Nepalese team who will participate in the Paris Olympics.  The term of the agreement will expire after four years. According to the agreement, Komorebi will also provide uniforms to the Nepali team for competitions held under the International Olympic Committee and Olympic Council of Asia. These include Summer and Winter Olympics, Summer and Winter Asian Games, Summer and Winter Youth Olympics, Asian Beach Games and South Asian Games.  At the request of the NOC, logos of other institutes can also be placed on the uniforms provided by Komorebi.  NOC President Jeevan Ram Shrestha and Nepal Judo Association President Deepak Harsha Bajracharya were also present at the signing ceremony held at the NOC headquarters in Satdobato.  On that occasion, NOC President Shrestha said that this contract has added a new dimension to Nepali sports.    Ballot Box Revolt: What RSP's breakthrough victory...  Warning, Threat or Opportunity? Nepal's major part...  Granary in crisis: Water politics leave Madhesh pa...  \\\"China stands ready to work with Nepal to carry forward the traditional friendship, deepen practical cooperation and advance bilateral relations\\\", read the statement.  Building Nepal's Digital Future  Fuel shortages in Nepal: A hidden threat to health a...  Second Innings of Balen and Gagan  Who will become Balen's cli